The paper discusses recent advances in visual object tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep learning techniques in tracking algorithms suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The applications of tracking in autonomous vehicles and robotics suggest that the paper may also belong to the categories of robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM).
